Title: Debt, Leases, Taxes, and the Endogeneity of Corporate Tax Status 
Abstract:
 We provide evidence that corporate tax status is endogenous to financing
 decisions, which induces a spurious relation between measures of financial
 policy and many commonly used tax proxies. Using a forward-looking
 estimate of "before-financing" corporate marginal tax rates, we document a
 negative relation between operating leases and tax rates, and a positive
 relation between debt "levels" and tax rates. This is the first
 unambiguous evidence supporting the hypothesis that low tax rate firms
 lease more, and have lower debt levels, than high tax rate firms. Copyright The American Finance Association 1998. 
