Title: Informed Traders and Price Variations in the Betting Market for Professional Basketball Games 
Abstract:
 This paper examines betting line changes from the opening to the closing
 of the point spread betting market on National Basketball Association
 games for evidence of informed trader betting. We show that within-betting
 period line changes significantly improve the accuracy of betting lines as
 forecasts of game outcomes. We examine individual line change magnitudes
 and show that these are directly and proportionately related to biases in
 opening lines. Further, line changes are of sufficient magnitude to remove
 these biases by the close of betting. We interpret these results as
 evidence that informed traders are influential in this market. Copyright The American Finance Association 1998. 
